      <!-- ACCORDION -->
      <div class="faq-accordion">

        <div class="faq-group" id="faq-account">
          <div class="faq-group-title">Account</div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">How do I reset my password?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Visit the <a href="/account.html">Account page</a> and click &ldquo;Forgot your oath?&rdquo;. Enter your registered email and we&rsquo;ll send a reset link within a few minutes. Check your spam folder if it doesn&rsquo;t arrive.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">Can I change my username?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Usernames can be changed once every 90 days from your Account settings page. Your old username becomes available to other players once changed.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">How do I enable two-factor authentication?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">2FA can be enabled in Account Settings under Security. We support authenticator apps (Google Authenticator, Authy) and SMS verification. Authenticator apps are strongly recommended.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">I was banned — what do I do?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Submit a ban appeal via <a href="mailto:support@ironveilstudios.com">support@ironveilstudios.com</a> with your account username and a detailed description. Appeals are reviewed within 5 business days.</div></div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-group" id="faq-technical">
          <div class="faq-group-title">Technical</div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">The launcher won&rsquo;t open — what should I try?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Run the launcher as Administrator, ensure your firewall isn&rsquo;t blocking it, and verify your .NET runtime is up to date. If issues persist, reinstall via the <a href="/download.html">download page</a>.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">I&rsquo;m experiencing high latency in game.</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Check the <a href="/news.html">server status</a>. Try selecting a closer server region in Settings &rsaquo; Connection. A wired Ethernet connection is strongly recommended over Wi-Fi for competitive PvP.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">How do I report a bug?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Use the in-game bug report button (<kbd>F11</kbd>) for immediate capture, or email <a href="mailto:bugs@ironveilstudios.com">bugs@ironveilstudios.com</a> with your system specs, a description, and reproduction steps.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">What are the minimum system requirements?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><strong style="color:var(--text-primary);">OS:</strong> Windows 10 64-bit &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong style="color:var(--text-primary);">CPU:</strong> Intel i5-8400 / AMD Ryzen 5 2600 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong style="color:var(--text-primary);">RAM:</strong> 8 GB &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong style="color:var(--text-primary);">GPU:</strong> GTX 1060 6 GB / RX 580 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong style="color:var(--text-primary);">Storage:</strong> 40 GB SSD. See the <a href="/download.html">download page</a> for full specs.</div></div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-group" id="faq-gameplay">
          <div class="faq-group-title">Gameplay</div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">How does the PvP flagging system work?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Outside designated safe zones, any player can be flagged for PvP. Entering contested territories automatically flags you. Unflagging has a 30-second cooldown. Players in safe zones cannot be attacked regardless of flag status.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">How do I join a guild?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Open the Guild panel (<kbd>G</kbd> key), browse available guilds by name or tag, and send a join request. Guild leaders and officers can accept or decline applications.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">What happens when I die in PvP?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">You lose a portion of your equipped gear&rsquo;s durability and drop a small percentage of carried resources. Death never causes permanent item loss unless you are carrying cursed loot marked with a skull icon.</div></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-question-text">How do I access the Voidrift region?</span><span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></div><div class="faq-answer" role="region"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Complete the &ldquo;Rift Seeker&rdquo; quest chain (available at level 45+) to unlock the Voidrift portal in Veilhaven. The zone scales to your level.</div></div></div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CONTACT SECTION -->
